    "canonical_statement": "The Trawinistic Laplacian extends the usual second-order diffusion operator to the singularly regularized Trawinistic manifold. It applies the Trawinistic connection twice while raising indices with the regularized inverse metric.",
    "technical_interpretation": "For a scalar field ϕ\\phiϕ, the Trawinistic Laplacian is defined by $\\Delta$Tϕ=$\\nabla$T\\_a$\\nabla$Taϕ\\Delta\\textsuperscript{\\{\\text\\{T\\}\\}\\phi=\\nabla}\\{\\text\\{T\\}\\}\\textbackslash\\_\\{a\\}\\nabla\\^{}\\{\\text\\{T\\}a\\}\\phi$\\Delta$Tϕ=$\\nabla$T\\_a$\\nabla$Taϕ, where $\\nabla$T\\nabla\\^{}\\{\\text\\{T\\}\\}\\nabla$T is the Trawinistic connection and indices are raised using the regularised inverse metric.\\\\\\"
  },
